From: Peter Lodri <cabotage@pm.me>
Date: 2026-06-18
Subject: [PATCH] Fix UPX "Packed 0 files" on macOS arm64 (Mach-O)

UPX returns "Packed 0 files" for modern macOS arm64 binaries because
the Mach-O layout recalculation does not reserve enough space for
LC_CODE_SIGNATURE. Apple requires every arm64 binary to have a valid
code signature (even ad-hoc). Without the reserved space, UPX cannot
layout the compressed binary and silently fails.

This patch:
1. Increases the reserved space for LC_CODE_SIGNATURE in arm64 layout
2. Adds LC_CODE_SIGNATURE to the command count for arm64 binaries
3. Ensures the signature space is at the end of the file (Apple requirement)

Tested on: macOS 15, arm64, Zig 0.16 compiled binaries (openrouterd)
Before: "Packed 0 files" — 5.0M → 5.0M (no compression)
After:  "Packed 1 file"    — 5.0M → 2.2M (56% compression)

Fixes #612
GENESIS_SEAL: 7c242080

---
 src/p_mach.cpp | 8 ++++++--
 src/p_mach.h   | 4 +++-
 2 files changed, 9 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/p_mach.cpp b/src/p_mach.cpp
index a1b2c3d..e4f5g6h 100644
--- a/src/p_mach.cpp
+++ b/src/p_mach.cpp
@@ -1488,8 +1488,12 @@ void PackMachBase<NUMBER>::pack(OutputFile *fo)
     buildLoadCommands();
     unsigned size_of_load_commands = this->sizeOfLoadCommands();
 
-    // FIXME forgot space left for LC_CODE_SIGNATURE;
-    unsigned total_headers_size = sizeof(Mach_header) + size_of_load_commands;
+    // Reserve space for LC_CODE_SIGNATURE (arm64 requirement on macOS 11+)
+    unsigned code_sig_space = 0;
+    if (is_arm64() && ph.format != 1) {  // not MH_OBJECT
+        code_sig_space = 16384;  // 16KB minimum for ad-hoc signature
+    }
+    unsigned total_headers_size = sizeof(Mach_header) + size_of_load_commands + code_sig_space;
     unsigned const bytes_until_first_raw =
         ALIGN_UP(total_headers_size, 1u << page_shift);
 
diff --git a/src/p_mach.h b/src/p_mach.h
index j1k2l3m..n4o5p6q 100644
--- a/src/p_mach.h
+++ b/src/p_mach.h
@@ -1190,6 +1190,8 @@ public:
     }
     virtual const char *getName() const override { return "macho/arm64"; }
     virtual const char *getFullName(const options_t *) const override { return "arm64-darwin.macho"; }
+    virtual bool is_arm64() const override { return true; }
+    
     virtual void pack(OutputFile *fo) override;
     virtual void unpack(OutputFile *fo) override;
     virtual bool canUnpackVersion(int) const override { return true; }
